value.0: Rafael sighs and puts away his coin as you come towards him.
"It is simply unnatural... So how can I help you, <FirstName>?"
An arrogant elf or half elf stands, running a coin through his fingers, then flipping it in the air and catching it as it spins.
"This coin has the face of an ancient emperor on one side and a fig leaf on the other. I have tossed it in the air 147 times, and each time it has landed with the face up."
"But enough of that. How can Rafael, son of Guildafa, and follower of Callahi assist you today? Perhaps you are here to visit the wonders of faith that I sell for a mere fraction of their cost?"
"Return should you wish to purchase some of the finest goods in the keep."
"What would you like to know?"
"Then perhaps it is time to view Callahi's wonders of faith, no?"

Comment.value: Set that one more priest supports vote for PC.

value.0: "There is only one thing that I and my god truly care about and that is gold. Sir Becket has paid me 1000 gold to try to change the priest guild vote. Unfortunately, the others have not been swayed."
"If you could persuade Lavos to vote for you, and if you pay me 2000 gold, I will add my voice to yours and we shall see what music we can make together."
"If you cannot afford the price, then you are undeserving of my support. One who could afford my price would show that <he/she> had the favor of my god."
"You must be favored by Callahi, to have such wealth. I shall tell Dynschall that I, Rafael, son of Guildafa, would have us vote for you. Hopefully he will listen to me."
"Anything less than double my previous bribe would be an insult to both Callahi and to myself. I shall continue to support Sir Becket, unless you can out bribe him."

value.0: "I have already said that I would vote for you. But I could flip a coin and change my mind, should you pester me about the decision."
"Yes! I sell only the finest religious artifacts, potions and other assorted items, and all at the best prices you can find. Would you care to purchase something?"
"Keep in mind that time is money! I do hope you will spend lots of coin at my shop when I have provided you with all the answers you need."
"Wonderful, I think you will find that everything you need can be found right here."
"Callahi is the god of the coin, patron of merchants, purveyor of luck, and father of the wealthiest priesthood in all the lands."
"As his priest, I sell wonders of faith for a reasonable profit and help care for the temple's wealth."
"Guildafa was my father and a hero of the elven people. My mother was a human, but I was raised by the elves."
"If my father had not been such a hero, I might have been shunned, but my mixed heritage was overlooked."
"Such a lucky person I was, quite naturally I worship Callahi, god of merchants and luck. As a priest, I have access to the wonders of faith, at the best prices."
"Good day,  my Lord <FirstName>. How may I help you today?"
